{"questionId":"9071413","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Urea, (H<sub>2</sub>N)<sub>2</sub>CO, is excreted by mammals and can be used as a fertilizer.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>The structural formula of urea is shown.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4562/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-09_om_13.51.02.png\" alt=\"M18/4/CHEMI/SP2/ENG/TZ1/01.b_01\"></p>\n<p>Predict the electron domain and molecular geometries at the nitrogen and carbon&nbsp;atoms, applying the VSEPR theory.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4563/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-09_om_13.52.37.png\" alt=\"M18/4/CHEMI/SP2/ENG/TZ1/01.b_02\"></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4564/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-09_om_13.53.16.png\" alt=\"M18/4/CHEMI/SP2/ENG/TZ1/01.b/M\"></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Note: Urea’s structure is more complex&nbsp;</em><em>than that predicted from VSEPR theory.</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[3 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9071413","referenceCode":"18M.2.sl.TZ1.1b","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"The structural formula of urea is shown. Predict the electron domain and molecular geometries at the nitrogen and carbon atoms, applying the VSEPR theory.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 4: Chemical bonding and structure","4.3 Covalent structures","Core","Topic 4: Chemical bonding and structure"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}